The paper deals with a proof system for higher-order logic modulo theories, which is a topic that falls under the category of logic and artificial intelligence. Therefore, cs.LO and cs.AI are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also discusses the compactness theorem and semi-decidability, which are topics related to programming languages and software engineering, respectively, making cs.PL and cs.SE likely sub-categories as well. Finally, the paper presents a variant of a well-known translation from higher-order to first-order logic, which is a topic that falls under the category of machine learning, making cs.LG a possible sub-category.
